.TH VACUUM-MAIL-APP 1 "May 2026" "vacuum-mail-app 0.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vacuum-mail-app \- vacuum the Mail.app Envelope Index SQLite database
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vacuum-mail-app
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vacuum-mail-app
asks Mail.app to quit without saving if it is running, then searches
.IR ~/Library/Mail/V<n>/MailData/
for an
.B Envelope Index
SQLite file, picking the newest data-store version present. It runs
.B sqlite3 vacuum
against that file, prints the byte counts before and after along with the percentage change, and
then reopens Mail.
.SH OPTIONS
This utility does not accept any command-line options.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
The database was vacuumed successfully.
.TP
1
The Envelope Index file could not be located, or
.B sqlite3
exited with a non-zero status.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/Library/Mail/V<n>/MailData/Envelope\\ Index
The per-account message index database that this utility compacts.
